title: For Sale:  Remington 750 Woodsmaster .243 with Burris Signature 3-9x50 AWESOME!
postcontent: Offered is my Remington 750 Woodsmaster chambered in .243 Winchester mounted with a Made in USA Burris Signature Series 3-9x50 scope. This rifle and scope are both in like new condition.  The finish is deep blue and is flawless, the wood is a beautiful walnut with a low luster satin finish. I purchased this rifle brand new 2 years ago, scoped it, bore sighted it with a laser at my kitchen table, fired 4 shots thru it in my backyard to confirm zero, then cleaned it, put it in a silicon impregnated gunsock, then placed it in my climatically controlled vault where it has sat untouched since. It is like new in every way. The scope is a Burris Signature Series 3-9x50 with a gloss finish that matches the rifle perfectly, the controls are smooth and function correctly, and the optics are crisp and brilliant. Burris scopes are fully warrantied by the Burris factory forever for any owner. It is mounted in matching Burris Signature Rings. GUN TESTS Magazine held a 'shootout' review between a Remington 750 the same as this model, and a Benelli R1 semi auto rifle and a Browning BAR II Safari semi auto rifle and the Remington 750 Woodsmaster beat them both hands down in every category; that is a pretty good recommendation for this rifle and what it is capable of. This rifle retails for $1004 according to the Remington website, and they are very hard to find like most semi autos now; there are also after-market 10 round magazines made for it. My price is firm but very reasonable, considering that the scope, rings, and base cost me $500. I will also include the box of Winchester ammo I bought with it, there are 16 rds remaining in it. I have the original Remington box and owner's manual. I will meet in a public place for a FTF cash and carry deal. I will not ship this rig out of state and the buyer must be a Maryland resident who is not prohibited in anyway from owning firearms. Please do not ask me to participate in any kind of strawman, third party, or out of state deal, and I am not interested in trades. Thanks for looking, pls email with any questions.
